This paper is about verifying the correctness of concurrent data structures, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses various formal foundations and techniques for verifying linearizability, which could be categorized under logic in computer science (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper compares the advantages and limitations of each method, which could be considered a form of formal methods (cs.FL).
